  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nCast\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n0.2.0\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\ncast age\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nAs per https://github.com/foundry-rs/book/pull/851, the documentation in the foundry book provides examples for `cast age` where the `--block` option is omitted:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ cast age latest\r\n```\r\nor\r\n```\r\n$ cast age 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is not actually working at the moment as `cast age` requires the `--block` argument.\r\nI decided to fix the docs accordingly, @mattsse confirmed this is rather a bug in `cast age` command (https://github.com/foundry-rs/book/pull/851#discussion_r1139371890).\r\n\r\n`cast age` should work without the `--block` option as shown in the examples above.",
